passages.text: Accelerating Into 2H with Faster Reflexes and Better Platform Strength

Solid 2Q beat with better than expected NNARR acceleration into the back half of the year. CRWD delivered better- than- expected results for 2Q with revenue, ARR, profitability, and FCF all ahead of consensus estimates. ARR performance was supported by traction with Cloud, Next- Gen Identity and NextGen SIEM which together accounted for more than \(\) 1.56bn\(of ARR. Underlying growth was supported by strong Falcon Flex traction with more than 1,000 customers now on Flex. Total revenue growth was also supported by stronger than anticipated Professional Services business due to greater than anticipated Incident Response business in the quarter. The stock initially traded off after hours as revenue guidance was a bit weaker than anticipated, with a lack of meaningful upside after this Q and Professional Services momentum that implies a softer outlook for Subscription revenue in the back half of the year. But CRWD also guided to NNARR acceleration to at least \(40\%\) y/y growth in the back half of the year driving total ARR growth of over \(22\%\) y/y for the year, which we think will mitigate some concerns around the company's ability to maintain \(20\% +\) growth near term. Management noted that confidence in NNARR acceleration is supported by 1) customers re- flexing at a faster rates than expected, 2) a strong pipeline of Next- GEN SIEM transition business, and 3) visibility into renewal business as customers lap CCP initiatives. The company's announced acquisition of Onum is not included in ARR guidance as the deal has not yet closed, but Onum could support better Next- Gen SIEM growth into next year. Fal. con could also be a positive catalyst and driver of better growth into FY27. This year's event is sold out at capacity of \(\sim 8,000\) and will be followed by a similar event in Barcelona which is shaping up to be \(2.5x\) larger than last year. Both events are healthy lead generation events for the company. We remain encouraged by ongoing platform traction as ARR acceleration supports an outlook of better growth and profitability exit rates this year. We are adjusting our estimates to reflect current period results and outlook and remain Overweight rated as we see evidence the company has been able to leverage incentives to accelerate market penetration, consolidate share onto its platform, and emerge as a dominant best- in- class platform.

Strong2Q results. CRWD delivered strong 2Q results with revenue of \(\) 1,169\mathrm{mm}(21.3\% y / y\) growth), operating margin of \(21.8\%\) and free cash flow \(\mu \mathrm{g} / \mathrm{in}\) of \(24.4\%\) , all above consensus expectations. On the back of better- than- expected results, the company raised the low end of its FY26 revenue guidance while increasing its FY26 profitability outlook. Management now expects FY26 revenue of \(\) 4,749.5- 4,805.5\(, implying\) 21\% \(growth at mid- point and operating income of\) \ \(1,000.1 - 1,040.1\mathrm{mm}\) , implying close to \(21\%\) margin at mid- point. This was offset by 3Q revenue guidance of \(\) 1,208- 1,218\mathrm{mm}\(below consensus expectations. CRWD expects to exit this fiscal year with a FCF margin of\) 27\%\$

CrowdStrike has established itself as a technology leader in the Endpoint Security market with a disruptive platform that has enabled it to penetrate core and adjacent markets with a high level of efficiency. Considering strengthening secular demand trends and an outlook that implies meaningful fundamental improvement, we continue to see opportunity for long- term upside with CrowdStrike.

Our Dec 2026 price target of \(\) 500\((unchanged) is derived using a 19.5x EV/ARR multiple on CY26E estimates (CY26 ARR estimate of\) \ \(6,309\mathrm{mm}\) . The 19.5x reflects a premium to large- cap high- growth software peers which we believe is warranted due to the company's status as a best- in- class platform vendor taking share across its markets. We believe our outlook remains conservative as we see greater potential for the company to execute toward our Bull case.
in Q4 with FCF margins expanding to more than \(30\%\) for FY27.

Falcon Flex adoption. On average, Falcon Flex deal sizes exceed \(1\mathrm{mm}\) in ARR, and over \(75\%\) of Flex contracts have already been deployed by customers to- date. CRWD added 220 Flex customers in 2Q, ending the quarter with over 1,000 Flex customers. The company is already seeing over 100 Flex customers engage to 'Re- Flex' which management noted yields a nearly \(50\%\) ARR uplift.

Emerging Product traction. Next- Gen SIEM, Cloud Security and Next- Gen Identity ending ARR grew \(95\%\) y/y, \(35\%\) y/y and \(21\%\) y/y, respectively and accounted for more than \(1.56\mathrm{bn}\) in ending ARR, growing over \(40\%\) y/y. Exposure Management surpassed \(300\mathrm{mm}\) in ARR. Multi- module adoption and attach rates remained robust this quarter, as customers with \(6+\) , \(7+\) , and \(8+\) modules now represent \(48\%\) , \(33\%\) , and \(23\%\) of subscription customers, respectively.

Guidance for 2H NNARR acceleration a meaningful surprise. Ending ARR was \(4,657\mathrm{mm}\) (growing \(20\%\) y/y) with NNARR of \(221\mathrm{mm}\) . Sequential NNARR growth was meaningfully better than the approximate \(6\%\) q/q growth rate messaged by management last quarter. CRWD now expects at least \(40\%\) NNARR growth in 2H with total ARR growth of over \(22\%\) for the year. CRWD guided to high single- digit sequential growth for 3Q, implying seasonally stronger NNARR performance in 4Q.

Lack of upside to FY26 revenue guidance. CRWD increased FY26 revenue guidance by \(6\mathrm{mm}\) at the low end while reiterating the higher end. However, ongoing Incident Response driven momentum for Professional Services implies softer than previously expected Subscription Revenue growth in the back half of the year. While the lower implied subscription outlook is a negative, we think guidance is conservative with the better- than- expected ARR growth rate offsetting.

Onum acquisition. CRWD announced an agreement to acquire Onum, a real- time telemetry pipeline management company. Onum's real- time pipeline detection is expected to deliver up to \(70\%\) faster incident response with \(40\%\) less ingestion overhead. Onum should help CRWD align with each stage of the AI lifecycle, ingestion and detection of data, filtration and optimization of data as well as actioning and enforcement to produce high fidelity autonomous outcomes across security and non- security use cases. CRWD expects to close the deal in 3Q and expects an immaterial impact on FY26 fundamentals. The company has not included the impact of Onum in the current FY26 guidance.

Impact of emerging products on 2H acceleration. Cloud Security ARR and Next- Gen Identity ARR growth rates have decelerated to \(35\%\) y/y and \(21\%\) y/y respectively, in part reflecting adoption as part of CCP initiatives. As the company has lapped the effects of CCP, we will look for indications of reacceleration of each in the back half of the year.

CrowdStrike has established itself as a technology leader in the Endpoint Security market with a disruptive platform that has enabled it to penetrate core and adjacent markets with a high level of efficiency. Growth is still expected to be among the best within our coverage, we believe the company can deliver FCF margins of \(30\%\) or better in the years ahead, and CrowdStrike has consistently been able to deliver fundamental improvement ahead of expectations as it is tracking to exceed its goal of \(\) 5bn\(of ARR by FY26. Considering strengthening secular demand trends and an outlook that implies meaningful fundamental improvement, we continue to see opportunity for long - term upside with CrowdStrike.

Our Dec 2026 price target of \(\) 500\((unchanged) is derived using a 19.5x EV/ARR multiple on CY26E estimates (CY26 ARR estimate of\) \ \(6,309\mathrm{mm}\) . The 19.5x reflects a premium to large- cap high- growth software peers which we believe is warranted due to the company's status as a best- in- class platform vendor taking share across its markets. We believe our outlook remains conservative as we see greater potential for the company to execute toward our Bull case.
